            "answer_text": "Length of the train, Lt = 250m Time, t= 30 sec Speed of a person = 6kmph Hence, S =D/T As we know, the train and the man facing opposite to each other Their speed will be added. Speed of train + speed of the person = length of the train/time Speed of train + 5/3 = (250/30)(18/5) Speed of train =24kmph. \ud83d\ude0a ",
